  "prompt": "How is Facebook going to help make Digital India?",
  "response": "Facebook (now Meta) has been involved in several initiatives to support Digital India, the Indian government's flagship program to transform India into a digitally empowered society and knowledge economy. Some key contributions include:\n\n1. Internet Connectivity\n- Free Basics program to provide internet access in rural areas\n- Partnership with Reliance Jio to expand digital connectivity\n- Investments in digital infrastructure\n\n2. Digital Skills Training\n- Digital literacy programs for small businesses\n- Training entrepreneurs in digital marketing\n- Skill development initiatives for youth\n\n3. WhatsApp Services\n- Digital payments through WhatsApp\n- Business communication tools\n- Information dissemination platforms\n\n4. Digital Entrepreneurship\n- Supporting digital startups\n- Providing platforms for online businesses\n- Investments in Indian tech ecosystem\n\n5. Digital Financial Inclusion\n- Promoting digital payment systems\n- Supporting small and medium enterprises\n- Facilitating online financial services\n\n6. Technology Innovation\n- Investing in Indian tech startups\n- Supporting local digital innovation\n- Developing India-specific digital solutions\n\nThese efforts aim to align with Digital India's goals of improving digital infrastructure, digital literacy, and creating digital opportunities across different sectors of Indian society.",
